Class PollReactionDecorator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jesus_crie.modularbot_message_decorator.decorator.MessageDecorator<net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.message.react.GenericMessageReactionEvent>
      • com.jesus_crie.modularbot_message_decorator.decorator.ReactionDecorator

          • com.jesus_crie.modularbot_message_decorator.decorator.permanent.PollReactionDecorator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cacheable

    public class PollReactionDecorator
extends PermanentReactionDecorator
implements Cacheable
    A persistent decorator that can retrieve the amount of the desired emotes under a specific message, like a poll. It will collect only the emote that are specified in the constructor that are added during the setup.

      • onTimeout

        protected void onTimeout()
        Description copied from class: MessageDecorator
        Triggered when the decorator times out. If this method isn't overridden, it will throw an exception but this method isn't called by default.

        On the other hand, an implementation like ReactionDecorator will call MessageDecorator.destroy() on timeout which is an expected behaviour.

        Overrides:
        onTimeout in class ReactionDecorator

      • collectVotes

        @Nonnull
public java.util.Map<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.MessageReaction.ReactionEmote,java.lang.Integer> collectVotes()
        Request the emotes under the message and count them, minus one for the base reaction. Calling this method too often can be costly since the message is queried from discord each time.
        Returns:
        A map containing the votes present on the bound message.
